Key Match Events: Maximilian Mittelstädt scored a superb equaliser for the EURO 2024 hosts
Niclas Füllkrug scored the winner as UEFA Euro 2024 hosts Germany came from behind to beat the Netherlands
Post-Match Reflections: Niclas Füllkrug has scored 11 goals in 15 appearances for Germany
Germany's record under Nagelsmann is: W3, D1, L2. They have won back-to-back games for the first time since he took charge
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was Germany's first home game since the death of world football legends Franz Beckenbauer and Andreas Brehme
Others: The Netherlands were quickest out of the blocks once the game got started, Joey Veerman scoring from close range after Memphis Depay had taken advantage of some uncertainty in the Germany defence
